<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,836,1979]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,836,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Aedeagal, median rod distally diffentiated into two strongly sclerotized, asymmetric pieces (ch.58-4; 
<figureCitation box="[151,237,872,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[180,1408,181,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phortica (Phortica) pappi (Tsacas &amp; Okada, 1983) (A; ♂ from Cape Tribulation, Queensland, Australia), Phortica (Ashima) machoruka Prigent &amp; Chen, 2008 (B, C; ♂ holotype), Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (D–G; ♂ ho- lotype) and Phortica (Ashima) afoliolata Chen &amp; Toda, 2005 (H; ♂ paratype from Jianfeng, Ledong County, Hainan, China). A, B, D, Periphallic organs (caudolateral view in A and D; caudal view in B); C, pregonites and hypandrial phragma (ventral view); E, surstylus; F, phallic organs (ventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed gd, aedeagal guide; aed m r, aedeagal median rod; aed s, aedeagal sheath; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd ph, hypandrial phragma; phap, phallapodeme; phap pr, posterior rod-like process of phallapodeme; preg, pregonite; postg, postgonite; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884620/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); arista with 4 or more ventral branches (ch.6-0; 
<figureCitation box="[796,886,872,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); hypandrial phragma broader than lateral gonocoxites (ch.41-0; 
<figureCitation box="[346,431,908,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[180,1408,181,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phortica (Phortica) pappi (Tsacas &amp; Okada, 1983) (A; ♂ from Cape Tribulation, Queensland, Australia), Phortica (Ashima) machoruka Prigent &amp; Chen, 2008 (B, C; ♂ holotype), Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (D–G; ♂ ho- lotype) and Phortica (Ashima) afoliolata Chen &amp; Toda, 2005 (H; ♂ paratype from Jianfeng, Ledong County, Hainan, China). A, B, D, Periphallic organs (caudolateral view in A and D; caudal view in B); C, pregonites and hypandrial phragma (ventral view); E, surstylus; F, phallic organs (ventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed gd, aedeagal guide; aed m r, aedeagal median rod; aed s, aedeagal sheath; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd ph, hypandrial phragma; phap, phallapodeme; phap pr, posterior rod-like process of phallapodeme; preg, pregonite; postg, postgonite; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884620/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,836,1979]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,428,944,971]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Shared characters.</emphasis>
Some interfrontal setulae as long as lowest setulae on ocellar triangle (ch.3-0). Arista apically without leaf-like expansion (ch.7-0); longest, dorsal branch longer than longest seta on pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,980,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Cibarial, medial sensilla all trichoid, apically pointed (ch.11-0; 
<figureCitation box="[883,974,1016,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Prementum without pubescent patches (ch.12-0). Pseudotracheae in labellum 6 per side (ch.14-2; 
<figureCitation box="[811,901,1052,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Setulae just before prescutellar acrostichal setae somewhat longer than other acrostichal setulae (ch.15-1). Mid and hind femora with gray patch submedially or largely dark brown (ch.16-1; 
<figureCitation box="[473,561,1124,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
); all tibia with dark gray ring(s) or largely dark brown (ch.17,18,19-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,1124,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Apical, downward curved setula on fore tarsomere V neither thicker than surrounding setulae nor longer than tarsomere V (ch.20-0; 
<figureCitation box="[351,438,1196,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Caudal bands on tergites III and IV medially interrupted/constricted (ch.21-2; 
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,1196,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Abdominal sternites III–V longer than wide; III not wider than IV; setulae on medial surface of III–V not so dense (ch.22–24,26–28-0; 
<figureCitation box="[380,470,1268,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype).A, Antenna; B, palpus; C, cibarium (dorsal view); D, proboscis (lateral view); E, fore tarsus; F, abdomen (dorsal view); G, legs; H, abdominal sternites. Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensilla; s c, sensilla campaniformia; s-I–IV, sternites I–IV; t-I–IV, tergites I–IV. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–D; 0.5 mm in E–H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884616/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). Epandrium widely round on ventral margin (ch.31-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1098,1188,1268,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[180,1408,181,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phortica (Phortica) pappi (Tsacas &amp; Okada, 1983) (A; ♂ from Cape Tribulation, Queensland, Australia), Phortica (Ashima) machoruka Prigent &amp; Chen, 2008 (B, C; ♂ holotype), Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (D–G; ♂ ho- lotype) and Phortica (Ashima) afoliolata Chen &amp; Toda, 2005 (H; ♂ paratype from Jianfeng, Ledong County, Hainan, China). A, B, D, Periphallic organs (caudolateral view in A and D; caudal view in B); C, pregonites and hypandrial phragma (ventral view); E, surstylus; F, phallic organs (ventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed gd, aedeagal guide; aed m r, aedeagal median rod; aed s, aedeagal sheath; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd ph, hypandrial phragma; phap, phallapodeme; phap pr, posterior rod-like process of phallapodeme; preg, pregonite; postg, postgonite; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884620/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); setae on and/or near ventral margin of epandrium not denser than those on other portions (ch.32-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1036,1124,1304,1331]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[180,1408,181,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phortica (Phortica) pappi (Tsacas &amp; Okada, 1983) (A; ♂ from Cape Tribulation, Queensland, Australia), Phortica (Ashima) machoruka Prigent &amp; Chen, 2008 (B, C; ♂ holotype), Phortica (Ashima) efragmentata Toda, sp. nov. (D–G; ♂ ho- lotype) and Phortica (Ashima) afoliolata Chen &amp; Toda, 2005 (H; ♂ paratype from Jianfeng, Ledong County, Hainan, China). A, B, D, Periphallic organs (caudolateral view in A and D; caudal view in B); C, pregonites and hypandrial phragma (ventral view); E, surstylus; F, phallic organs (ventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral view). Abbreviations: aed gd, aedeagal guide; aed m r, aedeagal median rod; aed s, aedeagal sheath; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd ph, hypandrial phragma; phap, phallapodeme; phap pr, posterior rod-like process of phallapodeme; preg, pregonite; postg, postgonite; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884620/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), longer than others (ch.33- 1; 
